item.description:
In thinking of new ways to waste time with extend emacs, I thought back on my brief attempts to use the color values from the DOOM theme collection to customize various faces. Fortunately for me, accessing the current DOOM theme&rsquo;s color palette from elisp is trivial using the function doom-color. Unfortunately for me, I don&rsquo;t always have a DOOM theme active&hellip;
Consider the following elisp:
(set-face-attribute &#39;org-verbatim nil :foreground (doom-color &#39;green)) All this is set the font color for org verbatim text to the associated green color in the current DOOM theme.
